<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="863" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d863">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-07-29"><hi rend="italic">July 29,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that an audience with the Sultan was granted to him
                            to-day and that he had a long interview with His Majesty, who promised
                            to give the pending question immediate consideration and to give a
                            definite reply to Mr. Leishman not later than next Tuesday.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>